description: The fund normally invests at least 80% of its total assets in securities that comprise the fund's benchmark index. The index is comprised of fixed-rate, Renminbi ("RMB")-denominated bonds issued in the People's Republic of China ("China" or the "PRC") by Chinese credit, governmental and quasi-governmental (e.g., policy banks) issuers ("RMB Bonds"). The fund is non-diversified.
name: VanEck China Bond ETF
